entry.title: iwa: Implement update discovery
entry.content:
This CL implements the first of two parts of IWA updates: Update

discovery. The `IsolatedWebAppUpdateManager` runs a repeating timer as

long as an IWA is installed to regularly check for updates. Update

checks are performed serially, so that memory and network usage is

spread out over time.



The `IsolatedWebAppUpdateDiscoveryTask` is deliberately not implemented

as a `WebAppCommand`, because it might take some time to download a

potentially big Web Bundle over a slow internet connection. If the task

was blocking all other actions on the bundle, such as uninstallation,

the user experience would unnecessarily suffer.



Bug: 1444407

entry.title: Parameterize suggestion behavior for manual fallbacks
entry.content:
As outlined in the DD, the flow of triggering and selecting suggestions

is the following:

- Suggestions are triggered through an AutofillSuggestionTriggerSource,

like clicking into a field.

- Suggestions are generated and sent to the external delegate.

- Once the user interacts (accepts or previews) a suggestion, the

BrowserAutofillManager is notified with the appropriate

AutofillTriggerSource. The manager then asks the driver to fill the

relevant fields.



This CL adapts this flow for manual fallbacks:

- A new AutofillSuggestionTriggerSource and AutofillTriggerSource for

manual fallbacks is introduced.

- Logic is added to the external delegate that converts from the

suggestion trigger source to the trigger source. It contains a more

detailed comment on this distinction.

This suggestion trigger source is available to the external delegate

through the popup controller, as refactored in crrev.com/c/4595077.

- The filling/previewing logic in the manager is adapted, such that

autofilling operations from the manual fallback AutofillTriggerSource

take ac=unrecognized fields into consideration.



The follow-up crrev.com/c/4549478 uses this mechanism to add an entry

to the context menu, which triggers suggestions through the manual

fallback AutofillSuggestionTriggerSource.



Another follow-up CL will use the AutofillSuggestionTriggerSource to

modify the profile suggestion generation logic. Right now, when

generating the suggestion labels, only ac != unrecognized fields are

taken into account. independently of the suggestion trigger source.

entry.title: [execCommand] Fix `RebalanceWhitespaceOnTextSubstring`

This patch fixes `RebalanceWhitespaceOnTextSubstring` when

`white-space: pre-line`.



It checks `white-space: preserve` and returns early if so in

This CL matches the WebKit behavior at:

entry.title: Use HandleKeyboardActivation rather than duplicating its code.
entry.content:
This chunk of code originated in HTMLButtonElement. In

https://crrev.com/8ebbf509126641fea90b694a58a3f98689d94cb8 it was copied

from HTMLButtonElement into HTMLSummaryElement (with no indication of

copying left in the code). In

https://crrev.com/93823ec8ea86211c97bf16a1e8bd0285b3a20189 the original

HTMLButtonElement version was refactored into

HTMLElement::HandleKeyboardActivation so that it could be shared with

HTMLPortalElement.



This change makes HTMLSummaryElement share that refactored version

rather than maintaining its own copy. Thankfully, the code is still

identical, other than the refactoring that was done to make it a

separate method.



There is also a more heavily refactored version of this in

BaseCheckableInputType and in KeyboardClickableInputTypeView that I'm

not trying to refactor here. The former was refactored out of

HTMLInputElement in

https://crrev.com/1e961c5625c998a178a3addc6ca60596e8c4b6b3 and the

latter was copied, likely from the former, in

https://crrev.com/4ac48dd80b65c4b827dee77a3562a2f414d0fe85. (Both the

original HTMLButtonElement and original HTMLInputElement versions mostly

originated in

https://crrev.com/689f576a65ae1a10943ba98b10621dec830d1e52.)



(In the future I would like to fix some bugs in this code, so it's

useful to have it in fewer places.)

tabs but is specific to a few specific paths of closing a pinned

home app tab.



This insight comes from two reverts on this CL [1] (due to failing tast

tests) and the explicit statement in this bug [2] that for example for

terminal apps the tab must still be closable. Therefore this check

should not be globally done in the `TabStripModel`.
